  "texts": [
    "As discussed above, we do this by removing the point corresponding to ξ + = 0 from the target space.",
    "We therefore also need to excise the pre-images from the worldsheet.",
    "We call the preimages z * a (a = 1,..., M) and so ξ + (z * a) = 0.",
    "The key point we want to make is that, in the bosonized coordinates, the points z * a must carry a background charge for the fields κ 2.",
    "We shall argue below that placing a κ 2charged state at z * a does two things; firstly, it ensures that ξ + (z) → 0 as z → z * a and secondly, it gives rise to the conformal anomaly of the radial Wakimoto coordinate Φ (see section 5.2)."
  ],
